Caption: Algira passenger moth [Dysgonia algira]
Description: According to Wikipedia, “the species was first described by Carl Linnaeus in 1767.” The larva is described to be “yellowish grey, darker on dorsum, with tine black longitudinal lines; venter and feet pale grey; spiracles black; head yellowish grey. The wingspan is 40-46 mm.” According to Wikipedia, the larvae feed on “Rubus and willow.”
